# Memory Recall

## Use this when
- The user issue resembles a previous troubleshooting case
- Prior cases may help narrow likely causes

## Procedure
1. Search for similar prior cases
2. Extract the prior question, findings, and answer
3. Use prior cases as supporting evidence only
4. Prefer current docs and diagnostics over memory when they conflict

## Rules
- Memory is not the source of truth
- Never present a prior case as definitive unless current evidence matches
- Say when memory is only suggestive
